# Synchronous FIFO (Verilog)

## Overview

This project implements a parameterized Synchronous FIFO (First-In First-Out) memory in Verilog HDL. The FIFO stores data in the order it is received and retrieves it in the same order while operating with a single clock.

The design supports configurable data width and FIFO depth using parameters and includes a comprehensive testbench to verify all major operating conditions.

---

## Features

- Parameterized Data Width
- Parameterized FIFO Depth
- Single Clock Operation
- Circular Buffer Architecture
- Independent Read and Write Enable Signals
- Full and Empty Status Flags
- Simultaneous Read and Write Support
- Pointer Wrap-around Logic
- Fully Synthesizable RTL
- Comprehensive Testbench

---

## FIFO Architecture

The FIFO consists of the following components:

- Memory Array
- Write Pointer
- Read Pointer
- Count Register
- Full Flag Logic
- Empty Flag Logic

The write pointer indicates the next location to be written, while the read pointer indicates the next location to be read. A count register keeps track of the number of valid entries currently stored in the FIFO.

---

## Parameters

| Parameter | Description | Default |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| DATA_WIDTH | Width of each data word | 8 |
| DEPTH | Number of FIFO locations | 16 |

---

## Module Interface

### Inputs

| Signal | Width | Description |
|---------|-------|-------------|
| clk | 1 | System Clock |
| rst | 1 | Active High Reset |
| wr_en | 1 | Write Enable |
| rd_en | 1 | Read Enable |
| data_in | DATA_WIDTH | Input Data |

### Outputs

| Signal | Width | Description |
|---------|-------|-------------|
| data_out | DATA_WIDTH | Output Data |
| full | 1 | FIFO Full Indicator |
| empty | 1 | FIFO Empty Indicator |

---

## FIFO Operation

### Write Operation

When:

- `wr_en = 1`
- `rd_en = 0`
- FIFO is not full

The FIFO:

- Stores `data_in`
- Increments the write pointer
- Increments the count

---

### Read Operation

When:

- `rd_en = 1`
- `wr_en = 0`
- FIFO is not empty

The FIFO:

- Outputs the oldest stored data
- Increments the read pointer
- Decrements the count

---

### Simultaneous Read and Write

When both `wr_en` and `rd_en` are asserted and the FIFO is not empty:

- Read operation is performed
- Write operation is performed
- Both pointers are updated
- Count remains unchanged

---

### Full Condition

When the FIFO is full:

- Additional write requests are ignored.
- Simultaneous read and write operations are still supported.

---

### Empty Condition

When the FIFO is empty:

- Read requests are ignored.
- If both read and write are asserted simultaneously, only the write operation is performed.

---

## Testbench Verification

The following scenarios are verified:

- Reset Operation
- Single Write
- Single Read
- Fill FIFO
- Write When Full
- Empty FIFO
- Read When Empty
- Simultaneous Read and Write
- Pointer Wrap-around

Simulation results confirm correct FIFO functionality for all test cases.

